Write the static method invert that, given a 2D int array pixels representing a grayscale image, returns a new 2D int array of the same dimensions in which every pixel value v has been replaced with 255 - v (its photographic negative). The original parameter array must not be modified. You may assume pixels has at least one row and one column and that every row has the same length.

reference_solution:
public class Image {
    private int[][] pixels;

    public Image(int[][] p) {
        pixels = p;
    }

    public int[][] getPixels() {
        return pixels;
    }

    public static int[][] invert(int[][] pixels) {
        int rows = pixels.length;
        int cols = pixels[0].length;
        int[][] result = new int[rows][cols];
        for (int r = 0; r < rows; r++) {
            for (int c = 0; c < cols; c++) {
                result[r][c] = 255 - pixels[r][c];
            }
        }
        return result;
    }
}

