A library tracks each physical book with a LibraryBook object. Each book records its title, author, the number of times it has been checked out over its lifetime, and whether it is currently checked out. Write the complete LibraryBook class so that the calls in the table below behave as described.

Method / Constructor signatures:
  public LibraryBook(String title, String author, int timesCheckedOut)
      - Constructs a book with the given title, author, and prior checkout count. The book starts NOT currently checked out.
  public LibraryBook(String title, String author)
      - Constructs a brand-new book with the given title and author. The lifetime checkout count must default to 0, and the book starts NOT currently checked out.
  public void checkOut()
      - If the book is not currently checked out, mark it as checked out AND increment the lifetime checkout count by 1. If the book is already checked out, this method must do nothing.
  public String getInfo()
      - Returns a String of the form: <title> by <author> (<status>), checkouts: <count>
        where <status> is exactly the literal "currently checked out" if the book is currently checked out, or exactly the literal "available" otherwise.

All instance variables must be private. Do NOT use System.out.print inside getInfo.

